<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-06-25T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-06-25T10:00:00-05:00" n="342" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d342">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">662.116 Lard/28: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dodd</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-06-25T16:00:00+01:00">June 25, 1934—4
                                    p.m.</date><lb/>[Received June 25—1:03 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>120. Agriculture Attaché in telegram No. 477, June 23 to the
                                Department of Agriculture announces prohibition July all lard
                                imports except from countries having special agreements.</p>
                            <p>Multiplication import and export restrictions points to early
                                establishment of central foreign trade control.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Dodd</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>